name: Sulphur crested Cockatoos
description:
Four of the Australian species are predominantly white in colour including the very familiar and spectacular Sulphur-crested Cockatoo. These noisy birds feed on berries, seeds, nuts and roots. 

Cockatoo facts
Cockatoos have a preferred “footedness” analogous to human handedness. 

Unlike humans, most are left-footed.

In captivity, cockatoos have a lifespan similar to humans.

The word ‘cockatoo’ has its origins in Malay and means ‘vice’ or ‘grip’ because of their incredibly strong beak.
